23/02/2007
ZAGREB, Croatia -- The fourth annual conference on border security in Southeast Europe began on Thursday (February 22nd) in Dubrovnik. Interior ministers of Albania, Bosnia and Herzegovina, Montenegro, Croatia, Macedonia and Serbia are participating in the three-day forum, which is focusing on the importance of drafting a common security strategy in the region and the role of border police in fighting organised crime and terror threats. 
In other news Thursday, the Croatian Interior Ministry announced charges against a 44-year-old Croatian citizen suspected of stealing diamonds worth millions of euros. They had been put up to guarantee the delivery of weapons to Croatia during its 1991-1995 fight for independence. (Vjesnik - 23/02/07; HINA, HRT, Focus, Tanjug, Makfax, MINA, Reuters - 22/02/07)
